				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Sandbox: Infantry Patrols in occupied territory – A campaign system for FiveCore" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Up ahead, it looks like a bunch of the locals are gathering. &amp;#10;Could be a sign of trouble, could be they need help with something. Never know in advance.&amp;#10;Second team goes to take a look while you hang back to keep an eye on things. &amp;#10;Suddenly shots ring out from across the street. We have contact!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sandbox is a mini-campaign system for FiveCore games (though it can be adopted to others as well) focusing on infantry patrols in an occupied city.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Inspired by infantry actions in Iraq and Afghanistan, it could be applied to theoretical, fictional or even futuristic peacekeeping operations as well.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Command your infantry squad as you move across the table, investigate designated points and try to roll with the punches.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you get in over your head, you'll be able to call in support... if HQ approves it.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sandbox uses random rolls to generate encounters, giving an unpredictable experience crafted to be particularly useful for Solo players and can be easily incorporated in a conventional wargames campaign.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Features include: &amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Rules adjustments for FiveCore to fit the setting better.&amp;#10;     Three different levels of enemies.&amp;#10;     A set of skills to acquire, specifically suited to the environment.&amp;#10;     Advice on how to scale up the campaign game to include bigger actions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
